{"action": "input", "code": "def set_elements_around_color(input_grid: np.ndarray, color: int, new_color: int, surrounding_color: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Sets the elements around a given color in the input grid to a new color if they are currently a surrounding color.\n\n    Args:\n    - input_grid (np.ndarray): the input grid\n    - color (int): the color to find in the input grid\n    - new_color (int): the new color to set the surrounding elements to\n    - surrounding_color (int): the color of the surrounding elements to check for\n\n    Returns:\n    - np.ndarray: the updated grid with the surrounding elements set to the new color\n    \"\"\"\n    output_grid = copy_grid(input_grid)\n    rows, cols = output_grid.shape\n    for i in range(rows):\n        for j in range(cols):\n            if output_grid[i][j] == color:\n                if i > 0 and output_grid[i - 1][j] == surrounding_color:\n                    output_grid[i - 1][j] = new_color\n                if i < rows - 1 and output_grid[i + 1][j] == surrounding_color:\n                    output_grid[i + 1][j] = new_color\n                if j > 0 and output_grid[i][j - 1] == surrounding_color:\n                    output_grid[i][j - 1] = new_color\n                if j < cols - 1 and output_grid[i][j + 1] == surrounding_color:\n                    output_grid[i][j + 1] = new_color\n    return output_grid\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = copy_grid(input_grid)\n    output_grid = set_elements_around_color(output_grid)\n    return output_grid\ndef copy_grid(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    return np.copy(input_grid)", "user_code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    output_grid = `copy of input grid`(input_grid)\n    output_grid = `set black elements around red element to blue elments, set black elements around green element to pink elements, and set black elements around teal element to yellow elements`(output_grid)\n    return out